# Mtphr Settings - Cursor Rules

## Changelog Updates
- When making updates to the plugin, auto-update readme.txt with brief bulleted updates below the UNRELEASED heading
- If the UNRELEASED heading does not exist in the changelog, add it to the top of the Changelog section and then add the updates
- Keep update descriptions short and generic

## Wiki Updates for Fields
- When adding a new field type, create a corresponding wiki page at `wiki/Field-Types-<Field-Name>.md` following the format of existing field wiki pages (description, usage, properties, examples)
- When adding a new field type, also add a link to it in the appropriate section of `wiki/Home.md`
- When updating an existing field type, update its corresponding wiki page to reflect the changes

## Documentation Files
- NEVER create .md (markdown) files for this project unless explicitly requested by the user or required by the wiki update rules above
- Do not create README.md or other ad-hoc documentation files
- Only create .md files when the user specifically asks for them or when field types are added/updated

